<!-- SC_OFF --><div class="md"><p>I&#39;m encountering a peculiar issue with cursor behavior in Emacs, and I&#39;m hoping someone can help me resolve it:</p> <ol> <li>When the cursor is on Hebrew text, it becomes completely invisible.</li> <li>This only occurs with the cursor type set to &#39;bar&#39;.</li> <li>The &#39;box&#39; cursor type works without issues.</li> <li>There&#39;s a similar, but slightly different issue with Arabic text.</li> </ol> <p>I use Emacs 29.3 for Mac. Changing font and bidi settings haven&#39;t solved the issue. Now I have no clue where to look for solution </p> <p><a href="https://e.pcloud.link/publink/show?code=XZBISgZw3lVDz5GqNyxxOOtwQCdGuIhtXWy">Here is a short video</a> to illustrate the problem.</p> </div><!-- SC_ON --> &#32; submitted by &#32; <a href="https://www.reddit.com/user/HermannSorgel"> /u/HermannSorgel </a> <br/> <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/emacs/comments/1e83mfx/cursor_disappears_with_hebrew_text/">[link]</a></span> &#32; <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/emacs/comments/1e83mfx/cursor_disappears_with_hebrew_text/">[comments]</a></span>